lead_paragraph: Prosecutors in Denver said yesterday that they had issued arrest warrants for seven people, including five current or former members of Colorado State, as part of a fraud and forgery investigation dating to last year. The prosecutor’s office said the felony charges ranged from forgery to theft to identity theft.
